ire, England","England":"England","Linton, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Linton, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Talbot","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Emile, Marcel, Anatole, Armand, Aubert, Camille, Gilles, Normand, Adrien, Alcide, Andre, Auguste.","English and Irish (of Norman origin); French: from the Anglo-Norman French personal name <i>Talebot</i>, a pet form of Old French <i>Talebert</i>, <i>Talbert</i> (see   Talbert   1). Compare   Talbert   2.","French: from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Talbald</i>, composed of the elements <i>dal</i> ‘bright, proud’ or <i>tal</i> ‘valley’ + <i>bald</i> ‘bold’."],"variants":[{"name":"Talbert","meanings":["English and Scottish (of Norman origin); French: from the Old French personal name <i>Talebert</i>, <i>Talbert</i>, from ancient Germanic <i>Talaberht</i> or <i>Dalbert</i>, composed of the elements <i>dal</i> ‘bright, proud’ or <i>tal</i> ‘valley’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright’.","Altered form of English   Talbot  , a cognate of 1 above."]},{"name":"Talbott","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Talbot  ."]}]},{"name":"Mabel","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a nickname from the Old French vocabulary word <i>amabel</i>, <i>amable</i> ‘lovely’ (akin to modern English <i>amiable</i> ‘friendly, good-humoured’). The initial vowel began to be lost as early as the 12th century (the same woman is referred to as both <i>Mabilia</i> and <i>Amabilia</i> in a document of  1185 ), but a short vowel in the resulting first syllable was standard, giving a rhyme with <i>babble</i>, until the 19th century, when people began to pronounce the name to rhyme with <i>table</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":80,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":89,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Mabel de Talbot was born about 1135, in Linton, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Sir John de Talbot Baron, was 49 and her mother, Mrs John de Talbot, was 32. She had at least 2 daughters with Richard Hussey. She died in London, Middlesex, England."},"et":{"about 1135–":"umbes 1135–Surnud","1135–Female":"1135–Surnud","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1135–Male":"1135–Surnud","1180–1225":"1180–1225","1187–1260":"1187–1260","1087–Male":"1087–Surnud","1105–Female":"1105–Surnud","1187":"1187","1087":"1087","1140":"1140","1260":"1260","1180":"1180","1215":"1215","1105":"1105","1225":"1225","1125":"1125","1224":"1224","1135":"1135","about 1135":"umbes 1135","about 1187":"umbes 1187","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Linton, Herefordshire, England":"Linton, Herefordshire, England","England":"England","Linton, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Linton, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1135–":"noin 1135–Kuollut","1135–Female":"1135–Kuollut","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1135–Male":"1135–Kuollut","1180